question: Rachel bought two coloring books. One had 23 pictures and the other had 32. After one week she had already colored 44 of the pictures. How many pictures does she still have to color?
response:
Rachel bought two coloring books, one with 23 pictures and the other with 32 pictures. In total, she has 23 + 32 = 55 pictures.

After one week, she had already colored 44 of the pictures. So, the number of pictures she still has to color is 55 - 44 = 11.

The answer is 11.
